    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Pre-fill canonical pattern" location="docs/guides/WORKSPACE-AI-PREFILL-GUIDE.md">
        Pre-fill flow: wizard captures document → `useAiPrefill` invokes
        `IWorkspacePrefillAi.PrefillAsync(...)` with 45s timeout → BFF resolves
        `Workspace:ProjectPreFillPlaybookId` → invokes `ProjectPreFillService` → playbook
        execution → `$choices`-constrained JSON output → `findBestLookupMatch` resolves
        wizard fields → wizard auto-populates. Every signature in this chain is
        BINDING-UNCHANGED.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Action row PATCH with binding-sensitive guard" location=".claude/patterns/dataverse/web-api-client.md">
        Same guard pattern as task 034 — GET by alternate key; check null; PATCH on null
        OR exact match; FAIL on mismatch. Capture pre-state for rollback evidence.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Project-prefill is the project-creation-wizard counterpart to matter-prefill (task
      034). Same architectural pattern, same NFR-07 binding. The wizard captures a
      project-scope document, the pre-fill flow runs, and the `$choices`-constrained
      output populates project wizard fields. Adding `outputSchema` to the action row +
      `destination = form-prefill` to the node is ADDITIVE METADATA only — the wizard's
      consumer path is unchanged. Form-prefill destination bypasses the workspace widget
      entirely.

      The risk this task addresses is INADVERTENT regression to the project-creation
      flow. Before/after test is non-negotiable. If migration somehow changes wizard
      per-field output — STOP, ROLL BACK, escalate. Schema declaration MUST be
      byte-equivalent to today's `$choices` contract.
    </background>
